The paper deals with constructing a matrix that can be applied to tensors efficiently while preserving their norm. This involves techniques from linear algebra, probability theory, and optimization. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.IT (Information Theory), and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves numerical analysis and optimization, which could place it in cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) or cs.SI (Systems and Control).
